## Technical Design

### Infrastructure Layer
- Image: ipfs/kubo:v0.26.0
- Network: Docker internal only
- API: http://demos-ipfs:5001 (internal)
- Storage: Dedicated block store

### Account State Schema
```typescript
interface AccountIPFSState {
  pins: {
    cid: string;
    size: number;
    timestamp: number;
    metadata?: Record<string, unknown>;
  }[];
  totalPinnedBytes: number;
  earnedRewards: bigint;
  paidCosts: bigint;
}
```

### demosCall Operations (Gas-Free)
- ipfs_get(cid) → content bytes
- ipfs_pins(address?) → list of pins
- ipfs_status() → node IPFS health

### Transaction Types
- IPFS_ADD → Upload content, auto-pin, pay cost
- IPFS_PIN → Pin existing CID, pay cost
- IPFS_UNPIN → Remove pin, potentially refund
- IPFS_REQUEST_PIN → Request cluster-wide pin

### Tokenomics Model
- Cost to Pin: Based on size + duration
- Reward to Host: Proportional to hosted bytes
- Reward Distribution: Per epoch/block

### SDK Interface (../sdks)
- sdk.ipfs.get(cid): Promise<Buffer>
- sdk.ipfs.pins(address?): Promise<PinInfo[]>
- sdk.ipfs.add(content): Promise<{tx, cid}>
- sdk.ipfs.pin(cid): Promise<{tx}>
- sdk.ipfs.unpin(cid): Promise<{tx}>

### Account State Extension
```typescript
interface AccountIPFSState {
  pins: IPFSPin[];
  totalPinnedBytes: number;
  earnedRewards: bigint;
  paidCosts: bigint;
}

interface IPFSPin {
  cid: string;
